The paper deals with the problem of implementing a regular shared register under unsynchronized Mobile Byzantine failures, which involves distributed computing and fault tolerance. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves storage and algorithms, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The problem of tolerating Byzantine failures falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves control systems and decision making, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves information theory and communication, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory).
